Description: Oval, dark red stone pendant or scaraboid with domed top: engraved with drill-holes on the base with a bird (a goose representing the 'sʒ' sign?), a branch(?) in front, a long object ending in discs at both ends behind its back. Behind this a double frame reminiscent of a cartouche in which some signs are inscribed, perhaps 'r' and 'n' or 'mn'. Hole pierced through longitudinally for suspension. Damaged - deposit or abrasion.
Bibliographic references: Giveon R 1985a / Egyptian scarabs from Western Asia from the collections of the British Museum (p.184, no.22)
